<h2>Fitting JChemPaint to your needs</h2>
<p>This section describes how JChemPaint can be customized to fit your working 
environment. Generally, custom settings are stored in your  <code>${HOME}/.jchempaint </code>
directory. On UNIX like systems, like SunOS, BSD and Linux systems,  <code>${HOME}</code> 
is something like <code>/home/user</code>. The value of <code>${HOME}</code> for your system can be 
looked up in the Info dialog from the Help menu.

<h3>Setting the GUI language</h3>
<p>The file ${HOME}/.jchempaint/properties has two properties with which 
your local language can be set:</p>
<pre>Locale_language = nl</pre>
<pre>Locale_country = NL</pre>
   
<p>This particular example sets the language to Dutch (nl_NL). The default 
language is English (en_US).</p>

